# War Room — Cursor context

## Production Environment
- Live at: https://warroom.codist.co.za
- Server: Hetzner VPS 65.109.7.45
- App dir: /opt/warroom (user: warroom)
- Containers: warroom-server (port 5050), warroom-client (port 3080)
- Network: warroom-network (isolated from Billable)
- Database: SQLite via better-sqlite3 (WAL mode), volume: warroom_sqlite-data
- CI/CD: push to main → GitHub Actions → auto deploy
- Workflow: .github/workflows/deploy.yml
- Nginx: warroom.codist.co.za → 127.0.0.1:3080
- SSL: Let's Encrypt (auto-renews)
- Shared VPS with Billable (app.mybillable.co.za) — fully isolated

## Deploy process
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build

## Never touch
- /etc/nginx/sites-available/warroom (nginx config)
- Billable containers or network
- warroom_sqlite-data volume directly

## Roadmap

| Phase | Status |
|-------|--------|
| 0 — Fix foundation, split components | ✅ Done |
| 1 — MongoDB caching | ⏭ Skipped — SQLite is enough |
| 2 — Session history + dashboard | 🔲 Next |
| 3 — Favourites + notes | 🔲 After that |
| 4 — Docker | ✅ Done |
| 5 — Hetzner deploy + CI/CD | ✅ Done |

Phase 2 is the next real unlock.

Right now stats reset every refresh. Session history means:
- Every problem attempt saved — platform, category, difficulty, time taken, solved/skipped
- A dashboard for weak spots — where you skip most, which platforms you’re slow on
- Visibility into improvement night over night

That turns War Room from a practice tool into a coaching tool — drill next from your own data.

## Coding expectations
- Match existing stack: React (Vite) client, Express server, SQLite (better-sqlite3).
- Do not suggest editing production nginx, Billable, or the SQLite volume by hand unless the user explicitly asks for runbook-only instructions.
